hat can be saved out along with the colored image. This allows you, if you have photoshop or a similarly equipped image editing program, to manually remove out the background. This tutorial will go into using the alpha channel to create a mask that hides out the ','Photoview 360: Creating a Transparent PNG','','inherit','open','open','','604-revision','','','2012-04-18 22:40:32','2012-04-19 05:40:32','',604,'http://solidwize.com/2012/604-revision',0,'revision','',0),(611,2,'2012-04-18 22:44:54','2012-04-19 05:44:54','<a href=\"http://solidwize.com/solidwize/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/solidwize-logo.png\"><img src=\"http://solidwize.com/solidwize/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/solidwize-logo.png\" alt=\"\" title=\"solidwize logo\" width=\"550\" height=\"250\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-609\" /></a>\r\nAn option to output an image without the background most definitely should have been built in to Photoview 360. At least SolidWorks creates an alpha channel that can be saved out along with the colored image. This allows you, if you have Photoshop or a similarly equipped image editing program, to manually remove out the background. This tutorial will go into using the alpha channel to mask out the background of a Photoview render and create a transparent png.','Photoview 360: Creating a Transparent PNG','','inherit','open','open','','604-revision-3','','','2012-04-18 22:44:54','2012-04-19 05:44:54','',604,'http://solidwize.com/2012/604-revision-3',0,'revision','',0),(609,2,'2012-04-18 22:44:48','2012-04-19 05:44:48','','solidwize logo','','inherit','open','open','','solidwize-logo','','','2012-04-18 22:44:48','2012-04-19 05:44:48','',604,'http://solidwize.com/solidwize/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/solidwize-logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(610,2,'2012-04-18 22:42:32','2012-04-19 05:42:32','<a href=\"http://solidwize.com/solidwize/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/solidwize-logo.Final-Color-Output.png\"><img src=\"http://solidwize.com/solidwize/wp-content/uploads/