r\n\r\n[slide name=\"7 day trial work you say?\"]With any subscription, you will have 7 days of access to all SolidWize content, after which your credit card will be billed. Cancel at any time during the 7 day trial and your credit card will not be billed.[/slide]\r\n\r\n[slide name=\"How does your 30 day money back guarantee work?\"]If you are not 100% satisfied with your Membership, just email me before your first month has finished and Ill refund your money, no questions asked. If youre not happy Im not happy. Including the 7 day free trial thats a total of 37 days to try out my training risk free.[/slide]\r\n\r\n[slide name=\"How often do you update your content?\"]New content is added on a weekly basis. If youd like to see any specific content added,<a id=\"contact\" title=\"Contact\" href=\"#\">just ask.</a>[/slide]\r\n\r\n[/accordion]\r\n<h3>General:</h3>\r\n[accordion class=\'accord2\']\r\n\r\n[slide name=\"What are the minimum systemrequirements?\"]Only a fairly fast internet connection is required for streaming. Almost any computer made within the last 5 years will work great.[/slide]\r\n\r\n[slide name=\"Can I log on from any computer, or just my own?\"]\r\n\r\nYou can log on to SolidWize from any computer with internet access using your username and password. Only one computer may access your account at a time however.\r\n\r\n[/slide]\r\n\r\n[slide name=\"Can I download the training videos?\"]\r\n\r\nAt this time, we only offer streaming video lessons. If downloadable content is important to you, please <a id=\"contact\" title=\"Contact\" href=\"#\"><span>let us know</span></a>.\r\n\r\n[/slide]\r\n[slide name=\"Do you offer educational or corporate discounts?\"]We do indeed! Please <a id=\"contact\" title=\"Contact\" href=\"#\"><span>contact us </span></a>for more information.[/slide]\r\n\r\n[slide name=\"Can I change my username?\"]\r\n\r\nUsernames cannot be changed at this time. You can however change the nickname that other users see in our community section by accessing the settings tab under the account menu on the right side of the upper toolbar.\r\n\r\n[/slide]\r\n\r\n[slide name=\"How do I change my password?\"]\r\n\r\nYou can change your password by accessing the settings tab under the account menu on the right side of the upper toolbar.\r\n\r\n[/slide]\r\n\r\n[slide name=\"How do I cancel my account?\"]\r\n\r\nAt the bottom of your user profile there is a cancellation option. Canceling a SolidWize subscription is an instantaneous and no questions asked process.\r\n\r\n[/slide]\r\n\r\n[/accordion]','FAQ','','inherit','open','open','','384-revision-5','','','2012-04-05 17:08:01','2012-04-06 00:08:01','',384,'http://solidwize.com/2012/384-revision-5',0,'revision','',0),(647,15,'2012-04-20 10:54:04','2012-04-20 17:54:04','<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">The Mission</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Our mission here at Solidwize is very simple, to get you learning SolidWorks as quickly and efficiently as possible, so you can stop struggling and start creating killer products. We are a small team entirely dedicated to that end, and as such we are able to quickly createvaluablecontent each week based on the immediate needs of our customers. Our users are part of the family, so if you have any questions about our content, your projects, or anything else going on in your life, we\'d love to help -<a id=\"contact\" class=\"contactform\" title=\"Contact\" href=\"#\">email</a>, call (877.688.7563)or post in our new<a title=\"Community\" href=\"http://solidwize.com/questions\">community section</a>.We\'ll get back to you as soon as humanly possible.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">The Team</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center; margin-bottom: 30px;\">Just two dudes who are really passionate about SolidWorks, teaching people how to use it, and building great products.</p>\r\n[one_half]\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: left; margin-bottom: 0px;\">Rohit Mitra</h4>\r\n<h5>Founder, Content Guy</h5>\r\nI got my start with SolidWorks after joining (and eventually becoming project lead) of my colleges Baja SAE team while studying mechanical engineering. After I graduated, I went to work for SolidWorks for a time before moving to the largest SolidWorks reseller to work in a technical support capacity. The best part of my day was helping customers design projects they are passionate about, so I started SolidWize to do that full time. I\'d love to hear from you, email me directly at Rohit@solidwize.com or follow me on <a title=\"Solidwize Twitter\" href=\"http://twitter.com/solidwize\">twitter</a>.\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: left;\">[/one_half]</h4>\r\n[one_half_last]\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-463 alignright\" title=\"me1\" src=\"http://solidwize.com/solidwize/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/me1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"298\" height=\"226\" />\r\n[/one_half_last]\r\n\r\n[one_half]\r\n<a href=\"http://solidwize.com/solidwize/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/andrewabout.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-643\" title=\"andrewabout\" src=\"http://solidwize.com/solidwize/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/andrewabout.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"298\" height=\"226\" /></a>\r\n\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[one_half_last]\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: left; margin-bottom: 0px;\">Andrew O\'Neal</h4>\r\n<h5>Co-Founder, Biz Dev Guy</h5>\r\nOnce upon a time I worked for one of the largest talent agencies in entertainment. After becoming jaded to the whole industry, I returned to my Silicon Valley roots. My background is in product development and web marketing. I\'ve pushed several digital and physical products to market, and after watching Rohit use SolidWorks to model one of my projects, I realized the power of the incredible tool and decided to help him teach others how to use it. My deep hope is that we can help you remove the frustration of 3dmodeling, so that you can more easily bring your projects to fruition. Email me at andrew@solidwize.com, any time.\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: left;\">[/one_half_last]